File: The SANDF says the culprits know the ins and outs of the base. PRETORIA - Twelve military staff accused in the theft of 19 automatic R4 rifles from a military base in Lyttelton, Pretoria have been released on bail. READ: R4 rifles stolen from SANDF military base The case has been postponed to 10 March for further investigations. Meanwhile, defence force authorities have hinted it may have been an inside job. It's believed the weapons were stolen between September and December.